# Arcadic critical surfaces — the forge gauge tripwire.
#
# A `git commit` that STAGES any file matching a glob below is a T2 track by default
# (design note + security & gate-integrity closeout lenses; ~/.claude/skills/forge/SKILL.md § T2).
# The commit is DENIED unless the message carries a `track: T2` trailer line, or the author
# deliberately gauged it lower and set FORGE_GAUGE_ACK=1. This forces a conscious gauge decision
# at the moment a security-load-bearing file is touched — it does not block the work.
#
# Format: one case-glob per line; `#` comments and blank lines ignored; `*` matches any chars
# INCLUDING `/`; each glob must match the FULL repo-relative path. Enforced by
# ~/.claude/hooks/critical-surface-gauge.sh (registered PreToolUse + git-pre-commit).
#
# Arcadic is a tenant-blind DB client, so the classic migrations/tenancy/money surfaces do not
# apply here. Its real critical classes are: boundary REDACTION (the value-free error contract),
# AUTH/credentials, statement INJECTION (interpolated identifiers + typed value markers),
# TRANSPORT security (TLS defaults, BOLT_* env hijack), and SSRF on import/export URLs. Each glob
# below is one of those classes. Conservative-complete for the known escape classes; widen on a
# traced escape, never speculatively.

# Boundary redaction — the value-free error contract. The recurring Rule-3 value-echo leak class
# (9x across S7-S13: FunctionClauseError/coercion-raise blame echoing params) lives at this boundary.
lib/arcadic/error.ex
lib/arcadic/transport_error.ex

# Auth / identity — login/logout, users, groups, API tokens, session credentials.
lib/arcadic/security.ex

# Connection — basic/bearer auth, TLS scheme selection (bolt+s secure-default), consistency headers.
lib/arcadic/conn.ex

# Injection — the allowlist/shape validation for identifiers that reach a statement by interpolation
# (index refs, order keys, groupBy) rather than as bound params.
lib/arcadic/identifier.ex

# Typed param value-wrappers ($int8/$bytes) — client-side range validation is the value-free/fail-loud
# guard that keeps an out-of-range value out of the server 400 that would echo it.
lib/arcadic/param.ex

# Transport security — BOLT_* env-var credential/port hijack, TLS verify_peer default, leak_safe_connect
# chokepoint; HTTP auth headers, TLS, and URL construction.
lib/arcadic/transport/bolt.ex
lib/arcadic/transport/bolt/*
lib/arcadic/transport/http.ex

# SSRF discriminator — IMPORT/EXPORT DATABASE URL handling and its allowlist validation.
lib/arcadic/import.ex
lib/arcadic/export.ex
